				<vgroup title="Textview" icon="19">

					<vgroup frame="true" frametitle="Textview demo">
						
						<textview styled="true">
							\33P[ff0000]Hollywood\33P[000000] is a \33bmultimedia-oriented programming language that can be used to create graphical
							applications very easily\33n. It was designed with the paradigm to make software creation
							as easy as possible in mind. Thus, \33P[ff0000]Hollywood\33P[000000] is \33bsuited for beginners and advanced
							users alike\33n. \33P[ff0000]Hollywood\33P[000000] comes with an extensive function library (encompassing over 800 different
							commands) that simplifies the creation of games, presentations, and applications, to a great
							extent. Having been in development since 2002 it is a \33bvery mature and stable software
							package\33n today.
							\n\n
							One of the highlights of \33P[ff0000]Hollywood\33P[000000] is its \33binbuilt cross-compiler\33n which can be used
							to deploy software on many different platforms without having to change a single line of the
							code. \33uThe cross-compiler can compile for all platforms from any platform \33P[ff0000]Hollywood\33P[000000] 
							is running on.\33n For instance, you can compile Mac OS X application bundles using the
							Windows version of \33P[ff0000]Hollywood\33P[000000].
							\n\n
							\33P[ff0000]Hollywood\33P[000000] is a \33blight-weight, but still powerful programming language\33n that is just about
							two megabytes in size and does not require any external components. Hence, it is \33bideal for
							creating programs which run right out of the box\33n. In fact, \33P[ff0000]Hollywood\33P[000000] programs will run perfectly from
							an \33iUSB flash drive\33n without any prior installation whatsoever. The following platform architectures
							are currently supported by \33P[ff0000]Hollywood\33P[000000]:
							\n\n
							- AmigaOS 3 (m68k)\n
							- AmigaOS 4 (ppc)\n
							- Android (arm)\n
							- AROS (x86)\n
							- Linux (x86)\n
							- Linux (x64)\n
							- Linux (arm)\n
							- Linux (ppc)\n
							- macOS (x86)\n
							- macOS (x64)\n
							- macOS (ppc)\n
							- MorphOS (ppc)\n
							- WarpOS (m68k/ppc)\n
							- Windows (x86)
							- Windows (x64)
						</textview>																																																					
					</vgroup>	
				</vgroup>				
				
